name: Dows Hall
directions:
Okay, there’s two bathrooms. There’s the one on the fist floor, and the one on the third floor. 

The first floor one is on the left as you enter through the front door. Walk down the hall till you get to the vending machines, and turn onto that corridor.

The third floor one is by the water fountains. If you use the stairs that are by the front door, it’s by the end of the Hall on the right. If you use the other ones, it’s n the left (and really close to you. Just walk past the fountains).
comment:
The first floor one is a single bathroom. It’s accessible, but there’s no changing table.

The third floor one has stalls (three of them) on the right as you walk in (on the left is showers). It’s not accessible, and there’s no changing table (and no elevator to get up there). Also, people live on this floor, so there’s probably gong to be at least one college kid in there.

name: Little Amerricka Amusement Park
directions: In the big red building by the main entrance, down the hall that is left of the counter where food is served
comment:
There are two single stall bathrooms, one with a changing table and one without. Be sure to check their operating schedule before you go, as it's quite limited. http://www.littleamerricka.com/info/hours
On the other hand, as long as you don't plan on riding any rides, you can literally just walk into the park. No lines, no admission cost. A ways to the right of the ticket booths, by the mini golf course, is a small staircase that you can use to easily avoid the long lines at the ticket booths and enter the park from the parking lot.
